When the *CamelCase Links* option is enabled, a page title that is in CamelCase format like "My PageTitle" will cause its children pages fail to render images attached to their parent.

For example, if a child page of "My PageTitle" tries to render an image attached to "My PageTitle":
{code}
!My PageTitle^image.jpg!
{code}

When trying to render the attachment, the wiki markup will change to "\!My gibberishstringherexoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxoxo^image.jpg!"

Dynamictasklist (Installed Version: 3.2.5 - Stable)is broken in tested 3.0.0_01, 3.0.2 and 3.1 environments using Internet Explorer 7(IE)

If you add a dynamictasklist to a page and add entries in Firefox (FF) it adds and moves entries as expected.  If you add a 2nd task list (including a title) it works in FF as expected.

However, if you open the same page in IE, the 2nd task list doesn't work at all to add or move entries around because the area you click to move a task is greyed out.  The wiki markup also shows that the macro call changed from dynamictasklist to tasklist in both IE and FF; is this normal?  If I try to add entries to the 2nd tasklist it won't add the entries in IE.  Basically 2 tasklists in IE doesn't work.

attached screenshot shows mouse cursor, but no options to delete/edit or move 2nd tasklist task.

Example code:
